USE_0006|Tc-99m DTPA|Which common use is correct?|Renal glomerular filtration imaging or aerosol ventilation imaging|Tc-99m DTPA can be used for renal scintigraphy as a glomerular filtration agent and can also be aerosolized for ventilation imaging.|2|renal_gfr_or_aerosol_ventilation
USE_0007|Tc-99m DMSA|Which common use is correct?|Renal cortical imaging for scarring, pyelonephritis, or cortical anatomy|Tc-99m DMSA binds renal cortex and is used for static renal cortical imaging, especially in pediatric applications.|2|renal_cortical
USE_0008|Tc-99m MAA|Which common use is correct?|Pulmonary perfusion imaging for V/Q scanning|Tc-99m MAA consists of macroaggregated albumin particles that lodge in pulmonary capillaries and are used for lung perfusion imaging.|1|pulmonary_perfusion
USE_0009|Tc-99m MAA hepatic shunt study|Which common use is correct?|Lung shunt fraction assessment before Y-90 radioembolization|Tc-99m MAA can be injected into the hepatic arterial system before Y-90 therapy planning to estimate lung shunt fraction and extrahepatic deposition risk.|3|lung_shunt_fraction
USE_0010|Tc-99m sulfur colloid|Which common use is correct?|Liver, spleen, and bone marrow RES imaging|Tc-99m sulfur colloid is taken up by the reticuloendothelial system and can be used for liver, spleen, and marrow imaging.|2|res_liver_spleen_marrow
